relevant_communication:
During 2018, NGO “Public Advocacy” so far has participated in a number of events at the European Parliament: “Christmas after Deash: Hope for Christians in the Middle East” hosted by MEP Maijana Petir and "Ukraine in the Independence time: The Orthodox Kyiv Patriarchate face to a changing society" hosted by MEPs Jan Olbrycht and Gyorgy Holvenyi, as well as in numerous events at the 37-th regular sessions of the United Nations Human Rights Council. 

Moreover, at the same regular session of the UN HRC written statements were submitted on the violations of rights in Ukraine and Israel (1. http://undocs.org/en/A/HRC/37/NGO/33 ;  
2. http://undocs.org/en/A/HRC/37/NGO/61 ;  
3. http://undocs.org/en/A/HRC/37/NGO/40 ;  
4. http://undocs.org/en/A/HRC/37/NGO/39 ).  

On top of that, NGO “Public Advocacy” regularly participates at the OSCE Supplementary Human Dimension Meeting (1. https://www.osce.org/pc/196246?download=true ;  
2. https://www.osce.org/odihr/188076?download=true ; 3. https://www.osce.org/ru/odihr/268206?download=true ;  
4. https://www.osce.org/ru/odihr/341606?download=true ). 

Personal meetings were held with high-level European officials: Her Excellency Deputy Secretary General of Council of Europe, Gabriella Battaini-Dragoni (http://spzh.news/en/news/48229-council-of-europe-will-consider-all-cases-of-discrimination-against-believers-of-the-uoc ) and His Excellency Council of Europe Commissioner for Human Rights Nils Muižnieks (https://spzh.news/en/news/48179-high-commissioner-to-consider-violations-of-the-uoc-believers-rights) . 

NGO Public Advocacy published its comprehensive report on the violations against the religious communities of the Ukrainian Orthodox Church during the period of 2014-2016: https://www.protiktor.com/app/download/6756821863/Ukraine+Orthodox+Report+2016.pdf?t=1524050898 .
